M|vercel-composition-patterns|Composition patterns for building flexible, maintainable React components. Avoid
M|vercel-composition-patterns|boolean prop proliferation by using compound components, lifting state, and
M|vercel-composition-patterns|composing internals. These patterns make codebases easier for both humans and AI
M|vercel-composition-patterns|agents to work with as they scale.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Reference these guidelines when:
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- Refactoring components with many boolean props
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- Building reusable component libraries
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- Designing flexible component APIs
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- Reviewing component architecture
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- Working with compound components or ctx providers
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| Priority | Category                | Impact | Prefix          |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| -------- | ----------------------- | ------ | --------------- |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| 1        | Component Architecture  | HIGH   | `architecture-` |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| 2        | State Management        | MEDIUM | `state-`        |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| 3        | Implementation Patterns | MEDIUM | `patterns-`     |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|| 4        | React 19 APIs           | MEDIUM | `react19-`      |
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `architecture-avoid-boolean-props` - Don't add boolean props to customize
M|vercel-composition-patterns|behavior; use composition
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `architecture-compound-components` - Structure complex components with shared
M|vercel-composition-patterns|ctx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-decouple-implementation` - Provider is the only place that knows how
M|vercel-composition-patterns|state is managed
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-ctx-interface` - Define generic interface with state, actions, meta
M|vercel-composition-patterns|for dependency injection
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-lift-state` - Move state into provider components for sibling access
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `patterns-explicit-variants` - Create explicit variant components instead of
M|vercel-composition-patterns|boolean modes
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `patterns-children-over-render-props` - Use children for composition instead
M|vercel-composition-patterns|of renderX props
M|vercel-composition-patterns|> **⚠️ React 19+ only.** Skip this section if using React 18 or earlier.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `react19-no-forwardref` - Don't use `forwardRef`; use `use()` instead of `useContext()`
M|vercel-composition-patterns|Read individual rule files for detailed explanations and code examples:
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
M|vercel-composition-patterns|rules/architecture-avoid-boolean-props.md
M|vercel-composition-patterns|rules/state-ctx-interface.md
M|vercel-composition-patterns|```
